      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE TAX CULLECTOR (7) led to win here three back and was good from this row at his latest appearance, finishing third and less than 3m off the winner. Drawn to enjoy a cosy run and if he gets the gaps he is a big chance. IM LORD TOMMY (10) made it two wins in succession at this venue when he led and got the cash by 2 metres last time out. May need an ounce of luck from this tricky draw but winning form is hard to knock. NIFTY STUDLEIGH (1) has been solid from wider or second row draws at Newcastle of late. Owns a decent record at this circuit and distance and should get his chance from the ace draw. CINNAMON (9) raced parked and faded last start but won two in a row prior, one of them from this row. Worth another chance.",
